  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 1</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 6</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b>  | <b>Successes:</b> </p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 9 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 21</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> M, F</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>The advanced Wato jumping technique gets his strength from the second jump made during the attack. The user makes a jump check counted as if he had running start to launch himself upwards, and then proceeds to make a second jump at -5 penalty to propel himself higher and proceeds to make an attack. For every 10 feet upwards that he jumped he gains additional 1d8 damage (up to 1 die per 2 levels) and additionally the opponent must make a fortitude save with DC increased by 1 per 20 feet that user jumped or be knocked prone and stunned for one round.<br><br>This technique counts as rank 9 for purposes of determining how long it takes to learn and master<br><br>Material Focus -The user's Wato, katana, double katana or hansori.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> : Chouten Tou Sei (3) and Sarutobi no Jutsu (5)</p>\n",
